  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Floor Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Floor Supervisor (Japanese Izakaya & Omakase)</strong></p><p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>• Supervise and support daily front-of-house operations across the Japanese Izakaya and Omakase</p><p>sections.</p><p>• Ensure smooth service execution while maintaining high standards of service quality, cleanliness,</p><p>and hygiene.</p><p>• Act as the main floor leader during service periods and support management in delivering consistent</p><p>guest experiences.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities – Service Operations</strong></p><p>• Oversee daily service operations to ensure smooth workflow and efficient table turnover.</p><p>• Coordinate service flow between Izakaya dining and Omakase seatings.</p><p>• Conduct opening and closing duties, including cash handling, shift reports, and service checklists.</p><p>• Ensure proper use and cleanliness of restaurant equipment and service areas.</p><p><strong>Guest Experience & Service Quality</strong></p><p>• Deliver friendly, attentive, and professional service aligned with Japanese hospitality (Omotenashi).</p><p>• Ensure accurate menu knowledge and service etiquette among service staff.</p><p>• Handle customer feedback and service recovery professionally, escalating issues when required.</p><p><strong>Team Supervision & Training</strong></p><p>• Supervise, guide, and motivate front-of-house staff during service.</p><p>• Support onboarding and on-the-job training for junior service staff.</p><p>• Promote teamwork, discipline, and service excellence on the floor.</p><p>Operations Support & Reporting</p><p>• Perform daily operational tasks and ensure proper documentation is completed.</p><p>• Report daily operational, staffing, or service issues to management.</p><p>• Carry out ad-hoc duties as assigned by the superior.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>• Minimum 1–2 years of relevant F&B; experience, preferably in a supervisory role.</p><p>• Experience in Japanese cuisine, Izakaya, or Omakase concepts is an advantage.</p><p>• Strong customer service, communication, and interpersonal skills.</p><p>• Service-oriented, responsible, and a team player.</p><p>• Able to work shift hours, weekends, and public holidays.</p><p>• Physically fit to stand and walk for extended periods.</p>",
